cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.LG

This paper deals with logical reasoning about program data, specifically heap structures, and proposes an approach that integrates Separation Logic and Satisfiability Modular Theory (SMT). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves programming languages and software engineering, which suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with formal methods and verification, which could fall under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
